 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To a young Lady who was going to India.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">SHALL we once more then meet on Albion's coast,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Before, my dear, in India you're a toast?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">There gilded pleasures wait your jet-black eyes,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And Asian youths for Scots Maria dies.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Yes! they may die — and die — and die again,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But ye's return and wed a Scottish swain,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+" line_length="4">Or wed him there.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
